g themselves ‘minor friars’ (<i>friari minores</i>). The main features of the Franciscan rule are humility, poverty, and love for all living creatures. The given name occurs occasionally in England as early as  1300 , and more frequently from the early 16th century, when there was a surge of admiration for, and imitation of, Italian Renaissance culture."]},{"name":"Frances","meanings":["Feminine form of   Francis .  In the 16th century the two spellings were used indiscriminately for both sexes, the distinction in spelling not being established until the 17th century."]}]},{"name":"Ulrich","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>uodal</i> ‘riches’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power’; the name of two major German saints,  Ulrich of Augsburg  (  d. 973 ) and  Ulrich of Cluny  (  <i>c.</i>1018–93 ), and the Blessed Ulrich of Einsiedeln in Switzerland (  d. <i>c.</i>980 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Frau Ulrich Stammler was born in 1248, in Ulm, Ulm, Württemberg, Germany. She married Ulrich Stammler in 1263, in Ulm, Ulm, Württemberg, Germany. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1248–":"1248–Surnud","1240–1296":"1240–1296","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1248–Female":"1248–Surnud","1248":"1248","1314":"1314","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1296":"1296","1240":"1240","Ulm, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ulm, Baden-Württemberg, Saksamaa","Ulm, Stadtkreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ulm, Oberamt Ulm, Württemberg, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1248–":"1248–Kuollut","1240–1296":"1240–1296","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1248–Female":"1248–Kuollut","1248":"1248","1314":"1314","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1296":"1296","1240":"1240","Ulm, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ulm, Baden-Württemberg, Saksa","Ulm, Stadtkreis, Baden-Württemberg, Germany":"Ulm, Oberamt Ulm, Württemberg, Saksa"},"fr":{"1248–":"1248–Décédée","1240–1296":"1240–1296","1264–1314":"1264–1314","1248–Female":"1248–Décédée","1248":"1248","1314":"1